cards.desc:
**Questions to ask**
- Other than group messaging and location sharing, what is the value that Life360 is or in the future planning to contribute to the world?
- Can you give me a brief introduction about Life360's location tracking system and how you optimize accuracy and battery life?
- What does an average day look like for engineers working at Life360? How many meetings do they have per week? What is the most common medium of communication? To what degree do they collaborate on projects?
- Ask about my relationship with the team and team's relationship within the organisation

**What am I not satisfied with Pixlee?**
- I'm actually quite happy at Pixlee. I've grown a decent amount here and we're looking to do some even more cool stuff in the future. But since this is San Francisco, there are always other people doing even cooler stuff. And I gotta keep my eyes and ears open.
- Since Pixlee was my first company and my bars about everything from the quality of code all the way to the culture of the company is set to Pixlee's standards. I want to explore more.
- I feel like I want an even bigger challenge to accelerate my growth.
- I don't get to go very deep into problems are Pixlee. Projects get done and being a startup we put more urgency into switching context and shipping something else and that code sits there.

**Why Life360?**
- I thought Chronos was a super cool app and I'd love a chance to work with the same team.
- I think location tracking accuracy is an interesting problem and working on it can enable me to grow in a way I want. Ability to dedicate myself to a problem and go deeper and deeper.
- I think I have an underrated sense of product and I'm excited about having an opportunity to work in a engineering and product combination role.
- More experienced team at Life360 which means more opportunity to learn from experienced people.
